          "body": "Verses 24-30 chain seven divine acts in unbroken sequence — the most compressed New Covenant text in the Old Testament alongside Jeremiah 31:31-34. (1) *I will take you from the nations and gather you* — regathering (v. 24). (2) *I will sprinkle clean water on you* — purification (v. 25). (3) *I will give you a new heart* — regeneration (v. 26). (4) *I will put a new spirit within you* — new disposition (v. 26). (5) *I will put My Spirit within you* — indwelling (v. 27). (6) *I will cause you to walk in My statutes* — Spirit-empowered obedience (v. 27). (7) *You will be My people, and I will be your God* — covenant restoration (v. 28). Each verb is first-person divine. Israel does nothing. The contrast with Sinai is total: at Sinai Israel said, *'All that the LORD has spoken we will do'* (Exodus 19:8) — and broke the covenant before the tablets reached the camp. Here God Himself is the doer. As Calvin observed on this passage, 'God demands nothing of us which He does not Himself bestow.'"
